text: Katherine "Kate" O'Connor (born 12 December 2000) is an Irish multi-sport athlete, active in the heptathlon and modern pentathlon. ==Career== O'Connor competed for Northern Ireland at the 2018 Commonwealth Games, finishing eighth in the heptathlon. She won a silver in the heptathlon at the 2019 European Athletics U20 Championships in Borås, Sweden. ==Personal life== O'Connor will begin a course of study at the University of Texas in 2019. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Living people Category:2000 births Category:Sportspeople from County Louth Category:Irish heptathletes Category:Irish female modern pentathletes Category:Sportspeople from Newry
